00:03.631 --> 00:09.975
?

00:11.677 --> 00:13.522
???

00:13.522 --> 00:14.754
????

00:14.754 --> 00:15.707
??

00:15.707 --> 00:16.879
what ???

00:16.879 --> 00:18.296
I ???

00:18.296 --> 00:21.222
?

00:21.573 --> 00:24.054
hey, can you please stop talking and smile?

00:24.054 --> 00:25.153
oh sorry

00:25.765 --> 00:27.579
huh,???

00:27.855 --> 00:29.822
?

00:29.822 --> 00:31.700
oh??

00:31.700 --> 00:33.533
TO PICK UP SOME REALLY
GREAT PIECES FOR THE SHOP.

00:33.600 --> 00:35.228
IT'S KIND OF SAD

00:35.228 --> 00:36.633
THAT THEY'RE
JUST GONNA SCRAP

00:36.700 --> 00:37.934
THIS GIGANTIC
THING.

00:38.000 --> 00:39.886
YEAH, BUT FIRST THEY'RE
GONNA AUCTION OFF EVERYTHING.

00:39.886 --> 00:42.067
PROMISE ME YOU
WON'T GO OVERBOARD.

00:42.134 --> 00:43.067
YES, YES.

00:43.134 --> 00:44.866
I KNOW WHEN
TO STOP BIDDING. SHUSH.

00:44.866 --> 00:46.400
NO, FOR ONCE,
I'M BEING LITERAL.

00:46.467 --> 00:47.467
I'M TALKING
ABOUT THAT WOMAN

00:47.533 --> 00:49.544
WHO JUMPED OFF
THIS SHIP LAST WEEK.

00:50.034 --> 00:52.167
DON'T YOU GUYS
WATCH THE NEWS?

00:52.233 --> 00:54.725
YEAH. ALL THEY FOUND WERE
HER SHOES BY THE RAILING.

00:54.725 --> 00:56.344
PEOPLE DO THAT
APPARENTLY.

00:56.344 --> 00:58.233
THEY JUST TAKE OFF THEIR
SHOES BEFORE THEY JUMP.

00:58.300 --> 00:59.600
OH, YOU'RE NOT JUST
BEING LITERAL.

00:59.667 --> 01:00.867
YOU'RE BEING KIND OF WEIRD,

01:00.934 --> 01:02.533
AND NO ONE
IS GOING OVERBOARD.

01:03.137 --> 01:04.167
ALL ABOARD!

01:04.233 --> 01:05.167
OOH. OK.

01:05.408 --> 01:07.208
DON'T FORGET
THEY'RE COMING SATURDAY

01:07.208 --> 01:08.925
TO DELIVER THE NEW
FRIDGE FOR THE GARAGE.

01:08.925 --> 01:10.233
I GOT IT. GO.
HAVE FUN.

01:10.300 --> 01:11.333
BYE, D.
BYE.

01:11.802 --> 01:13.949
HAVEN'T TOLD HER
WE'RE TRYING TO GET PREGNANT?

01:13.949 --> 01:15.318
I DON'T WANT TO MAKE
AN ANNOUNCEMENT

01:15.318 --> 01:16.607
UNTIL THERE'S
SOMETHING TO ANNOUNCE.

01:16.607 --> 01:18.333
BUT YOU KNOW, 3 DAYS,
THE OPEN SEA,

01:18.400 --> 01:19.934
WITH NOTHING ELSE TO DO.

01:20.000 --> 01:21.134
NO AUCTION PREVIEW?

01:21.759 --> 01:23.734
EVERY NOW AND THEN, YOU
HAVE TO TAKE A BREAK.

01:23.800 --> 01:24.967
OH, DO YOU?

01:28.600 --> 01:30.012
OHH.

01:33.134 --> 01:34.853
DID YOUR GHOST-DAR
GO PING?

01:38.233 --> 01:40.088
THERE MAY BE ONE OR...

01:42.533 --> 01:43.467
20.

01:44.037 --> 01:46.034
FINALLY.
SOMEBODY WHO CAN SEE US.

01:46.101 --> 01:48.233
OH, DON'T MIND THEM.
THEY'RE ALL ON EDGE

01:48.300 --> 01:49.867
ABOUT THE SHIP
GOING TO THE BREAKERS,

01:49.934 --> 01:52.467
BUT ALL GOOD PARTIES
HAVE TO END, RIGHT?

01:52.533 --> 01:54.233
WELCOME ABOARD.
I'M BETTY.

01:54.601 --> 01:57.067
UM, MELINDA.

01:57.134 --> 01:58.400
WHAT HAPPENED
TO YOU?

01:58.467 --> 02:00.366
OH. PHEW. SO SORRY.

02:00.433 --> 02:04.215
I WAS DEAD IN MY STATEROOM
BEFORE THE STEWARD FOUND ME.

02:04.400 --> 02:06.834
BLOOD SETTLED
TO THAT SIDE.

02:06.900 --> 02:09.773
MY ADVICE-IF YOU'RE HAVING
A MASSIVE CORONARY,

02:09.773 --> 02:12.333
DON'T PUT THE "DO NOT
DISTURB" SIGN OUT FIRST.

02:12.400 --> 02:15.230
<i>NOW, COME ON.
YOU'RE GONNA LOVE THE CLARIDON.</i>

02:15.230 --> 02:16.800
I ALREADY DO.

02:16.867 --> 02:18.366
YOU MAKING FRIENDS
ALREADY?

02:18.433 --> 02:20.733
YEAH, ONE THAT'S
ACTUALLY NICE.

02:21.367 --> 02:23.156
SO YOU'VE BEEN HERE
SINCE THE FIFTIES?

02:23.156 --> 02:24.800
NO. GOD, NO.

02:24.867 --> 02:27.333
'99. I WAS A VINTAGE-CLOTHING DEALER.

02:27.400 --> 02:29.167
SO YOU SAID
YOU'RE IN M-110?

02:29.233 --> 02:30.633
OH,
IT'S A LOVELY ROOM.

02:30.700 --> 02:32.338
AUDREY HEPBURN
ONCE STAYED THERE.

02:32.338 --> 02:33.631
YOU REMIND ME
OF HER.

02:33.631 --> 02:35.292
IT'S JUST UP AHEAD
ON THE RIGHT.

02:35.292 --> 02:36.600
OH, GOD.

02:36.667 --> 02:38.888
NOT NOW, MR. LINARCOS.

02:39.767 --> 02:41.433
LIKE I SAID,
THEY'RE ALL RESTLESS,

02:41.500 --> 02:43.233
WORRIED THAT WHEN
THE SHIP IS DESTROYED,

02:43.300 --> 02:44.734
THEY'LL BE LOST FOREVER.

02:44.800 --> 02:46.700
Woman: WELL, BRIBE THE STEWARD.
I CAN'T STAND OUR ROOM ANYMORE.

02:46.767 --> 02:47.834
AT LEAST YOU CAN
BREATHE IN HERE.

02:47.900 --> 02:49.167
Man: THE SHIP'S
SOLD OUT.

02:49.233 --> 02:51.000
WHOEVER BOOKED THIS ROOM
IS GONNA BE HERE ANY MINUTE.

02:51.067 --> 02:52.000
THEN WE SHOULD HURRY.

02:52.067 --> 02:55.667
UH, HI. I THINK
THIS IS OUR ROOM. HEH.

02:56.253 --> 02:58.034
RIGHT. SORRY.

02:58.330 --> 03:00.033
we were...  just um..

03:00.033 --> 03:01.400
BEING NOSY. HEH.

03:01.973 --> 03:04.101
HI. I'M RICH HENDERSON,

03:04.167 --> 03:07.193
AND THIS IS MY FIANCÉE-
I MEAN-HEH-MY WIFE.

03:07.193 --> 03:10.167
JULIA. IT'S HARD TO TELL,
BUT WE'RE ON OUR HONEYMOON.

03:10.233 --> 03:11.433
AWW.
CONGRATULATIONS.

03:11.500 --> 03:14.037
I- I'M MELINDA, AND THIS
IS MY HUSBAND JIM.

03:14.467 --> 03:16.667
WE'RE IN-IN 108,
RIGHT NEXT DOOR.

03:16.734 --> 03:19.067
OH. HAVE YOU GUYS BEEN HERE
SINCE THE START OF THE TRIP?

03:19.134 --> 03:20.644
SOUTHAMPTON
TO HALIFAX,

03:20.644 --> 03:21.972
AND NOW HERE WE ARE.

03:21.972 --> 03:24.101
RICH'S IDEA.
HE'S SORT OF A SHIP GEEK.

03:24.167 --> 03:27.134
PERSONALLY, YOU CAN'T SCRAP
THE OLD TUB FAST ENOUGH FOR ME.

03:27.201 --> 03:29.867
<i>THE S.S. CLARIDON IS ONE OF
THE LAST TRUE OCEAN LINERS.</i>

03:29.934 --> 03:31.134
AND IF WE DIDN'T
TAKE THIS TRIP NOW-

03:31.201 --> 03:32.931
THEN WE'D BE
ON A BEACH IN MAUl.

03:33.333 --> 03:36.206
I WARN YOU, IF YOUR A.C.
IS ANYTHING LIKE OURS,

03:36.206 --> 03:38.201
KEEP YOUR UNDERWEAR
IN THE MINIBAR.

03:38.876 --> 03:40.281
Rich: SO SORRY.

03:40.281 --> 03:41.500
BON VOYAGE.

03:49.208 --> 03:51.119
OOH, I AM
SO SORRY I'M LATE.

03:51.791 --> 03:54.727
DID YOU KNOW THAT THERE
ARE OVER 55 KINDS

03:54.727 --> 03:56.998
<i>OF EXOTIC WOODS
ON THE S.S. CLARIDON?</i>

03:56.998 --> 03:59.474
YOU KNOW, I'VE BEEN READING ABOUT
THIS FOR THE LAST, UM, HALF AN HOUR.

03:59.474 --> 04:01.311
OH, I SWEAR
I TRIED TO TEXT YOU.

04:01.499 --> 04:04.165
YEAH, CELL SERVICE
IS SO SPOTTY ON THE HIGH SEAS.

04:05.201 --> 04:06.700
WHAT HAPPENED?

04:06.767 --> 04:08.800
WELL, THE SPA WAS A ZOO,

04:08.867 --> 04:11.600
AND THEIR BEST MASSEUR
QUIT IN HALIFAX,

04:11.667 --> 04:16.075
BUT THERE IS STILL TIME FOR A
ROMANTIC STROLL BEFORE DINNER.

04:16.384 --> 04:18.312
DO I HAVE TO WEAR
A PENGUIN SUIT FOR THAT?

04:18.312 --> 04:20.166
NO. FIRST NIGHT, IT'S
JUST JACKET AND TIE,

04:20.166 --> 04:21.879
AND DON'T WORRY, 'CAUSE
YOU WON'T BE IN IT LONG.

04:21.879 --> 04:23.800
OH. SO THERE'S AN UPSIDE.

04:25.724 --> 04:28.300
YOU KNOW, I NEVER TAKE FOR
GRANTED HOW LUCKY WE ARE.

04:28.800 --> 04:30.331
ME EITHER.

04:31.202 --> 04:33.034
OK, WHAT ARE WE
TALKIN' ABOUT HERE?

04:33.101 --> 04:35.433
WELL, I RAN INTO JULIA
AT THE SPA,

04:35.500 --> 04:37.763
AND SHE KEPT APOLOGIZING
FOR TRYING TO STEAL OUR ROOM,

04:37.763 --> 04:41.000
BUT I GUESS THEY'RE HAVING
SOME PROBLEMS, YOU KNOW, IN BED.

04:41.067 --> 04:42.266
OHH. ON THEIR HONEYMOON?
YIKES.

04:42.333 --> 04:44.300
I KNOW. I GUESS EVERY
TIME IT GETS ROMANTIC,

04:44.366 --> 04:45.704
HE FALLS ASLEEP.

04:45.704 --> 04:47.040
THAT'S WHY THEY
WANTED TO SWITCH,

04:47.040 --> 04:48.108
'CAUSE IT WAS TOO HOT.

04:48.108 --> 04:49.881
OR NOT HOT ENOUGH
BY THE LOOKS OF IT.

04:49.881 --> 04:52.433
YOU KNOW,
YOU DO HAVE A SPOOKY KNACK

04:52.500 --> 04:54.400
FOR GETTING PEOPLE
TO OPEN UP TO YOU.

04:54.467 --> 04:56.433
YEAH. EXCEPT USUALLY
IT'S AFTER THEY'VE DIED.

04:56.500 --> 04:57.667
HMM.

05:00.134 --> 05:01.700
OH.

05:02.323 --> 05:04.098
POOR GUY.
WHAT'S WRONG WITH HIM?

05:04.098 --> 05:05.266
I MEAN, IS HE SICK,

05:05.333 --> 05:07.662
IS IT JUST THE PRESSURE
FROM THE HONEYMOON, OR WHAT?

